Rating: 3
I simplified this recipe. The flavor is very bold, but salad doesn't get "dry" the next day. Use only 8-16 oz. of pasta for this amount of dressing. Add cooked chicken, cilantro, sliced green onions, shredded carrots and/or cabbage. Mix dressing, combine with salad and chill. Serve with crunchy chow mein noodles on top.

Rating: 3
This recipe is great as a starting point but to make this salad exceptional marinate the chicken breast in a garlic soy sauce and grill. Add a red bell pepper, half a cucumber, a grated carrot and cilantro. The added colors from the vegetables and flavor of the cilantro makes this salad jump out at you. I've made this salad multiple times this way and it's always a hit.

