Rating: 3
I quartered the recipe and it made enough for my two teenage children and I to take in Gladware on a long JetBlue flight. We really enjoyed it above the clouds, but I finally figured out what was missing- the ginger! The 2nd time I made it, I added about 2 T. fresh ginger into a quarter-recipe of the dressing. Also I added 1/2 head of chopped Napa cabbage to the whole thing, which stretches it further. THEN it's perfect. I'd say a full recipe might feed 12, though, not 20 as a main course.

