Rating: 3
I was looking for a recipe similar to one a local restaurant serves, and this one fit the bill. Based on the comments, I had chopped peanuts, crispy noodles, and toasted sesame seeds available for garnish. I personally think it needed no more than the sesame seeds. I also added thinly sliced carrots, blanching them with the snow peas. The snow peas were actually the part I wasn't impressed with. I didn't think the thin slices with all of the loose little pea pieces was as attractive as leaving them whole would have been. In addition, they really wilt down and lose color the next day, again not very attractive. Next time I will probably leave them out and go just with the carrots. The cilantro already gives some green to the salad, so color is not lost without the snow peas. Just an opinion. Overall, this is an excellent summer dish and travels well!

