Rating: 4
I'm very sparing with my 4-fork ratings, but this was definitely one. Use a combo of soba, udon, & somen noodles for nice color/texture. Add chopped seeded cucumbers and red peppers. Omit the jalapenos and substitute some Chinese chilli sauce for it, mixed in with the dressing; taste dressing before adding to salad, adjust w/sugar, soy sauce, water, chilli sauce to taste. Use LOTS of cilantro. A big hit among both the Americans and Asians at the picnic we went to.

